Q4: What happens if I leave before my vesting period ends?\nA: Vesting may continue until completion depending on company policy. Please consult with your manager or HR representative for specific details regarding early termination.\n',
'prompt': 'I need a concise summary of how new hires receive their restricted stock unit awards and when they become vested. Include information on conversions, award determination, and visibility in financial accounts.'}
 New Hires receive their RSU awards through a process that involves converting the grant target value into U.S. dollars using the 9-month average exchange rate at the end of the Hooli fiscal quarter during which they start employment. This dollar amount is then divided by the average closing price of Hooli's stock over the last 21 trading days of the month of employment to determine the number of RSUs awarded, rounding down to the nearest whole unit. These awards are typically reflected in the employee's Schwab account once they become vested, usually within the second week of the month after the grant date. Vesting continues even if the employee leaves before completing the full period, subject to company policies.

